HEADWORD: Gapingstock
<hw>Gap"ing*stock`</hw> <pr>(? ⟦or⟧ ?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>One who
is an object of open-mouthed wonder.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I was to be a <qex>gapingstock</qex> and a scorn to the young
volunteers.</q> <rj><qau>Godwin.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Gap-toothed</ent>⟦br⟧
